title: Scotts Valley Grand Prix

address.street: 200 El Pueblo Drive, Scotts Valley, CA 95066

description: The Scotts Valley Grand Prix is back for its second run at lighting up the Twilight Sky of the Santa Cruz mountains. This race brings top-level bike racing to Northern California like youve never seen or felt before!!!
course:
Course: A one mile (1.6km) circuit in the business district of Scotts Valley which runs clockwise on El Pueblo Drive, Carbonero Way, and Scotts Valley Drive with full road closure. The road surface is good and the course features long straights, three turns, and one chicane toward the start/finish. 
Registration and the Start/Finish are located at 4900 Scotts Valley Drive.
registration:
Races with \"*\" are raced together, but scored separately. 
Held Under USA Cycling permit # 2011-575  USAC license required and must present a current USA Cycling license at registration  Annual license also available day of race  No phone or faxed entries will be accepted.  All participants will sign a waiver/release form at registration (or pre-signed by a parent/guardian)  Riders must wear a helmet that meets USA Cycling requirements. Registration fee includes $3 USAC insurance surcharge and $1 NCNCA surcharge. Entry fee does not include on-line registration fee  Day of race registration add an additional $7.00.  **Listed prizes are 100% cash value for P/1/2 and W/1/2/3.  Other categories may have a mix of Merchandise and cash as purse.  Juniors (15-18) May compete in their numerical Category.  Champions Jersey awarded to each category winner.  Riders winning more than $600.00 will be required to fill out a W-9 and may receive compensation in check form post event.

Register online: http://www.truesport.com  Pre-registration closes 5/12/2011 9:00PM PDT
On-site Registration opens at 11:45am, closes 15 minutes before each race. 
If entering two races, the second race of lesser price is discounted 50% (excluding late fees).
All eligible divisions will be counted toward NCNCA BAR and BAT rankings.
notes: No refunds! Event held rain or shine For more info: http://scottsvalleygrandprix.com/ NOTE: Registration opens 3/22/2011 - Riders who register BEFORE April 15th receive a $5.00 discount. Riders who show up to the event with their VALID bib# from Cats Hill (May 14th, 2011). will receive an additional $5.00 refund on day of race.
directions: Directions from San Jose take CA-17S Exit 5 Head southwest on Exit 5 toward Scotts Valley Dr - go 0.2mi Turn left at Scotts Valley Dr - go 1.2mi Make a U-turn at Civic Center Drive and follow signs to course parking NOTE: Traffic may heavy from 11:00am to 2:00pm on CA-17S (beach traffic to Santa Cruz), so plan accordingly. If your race is between 1:00 - 3:00pm, try to arrive 1.5 hours prior to avoid any traffic delays. Directions from Santa Cruz take CA-17 N take exit 3 for Mt Hermon Rd - go 0.1mi Turn right at Mt Hermon Rd - go 0.4mi Take the 3rd light onto Scotts Valley Dr - go 0.8mi Pass Civic Center Drive intersection and follow signs to course parking Parking available south of course and some areas on the northbound straight of Scotts Valley Drive. Follow signs for registration NO WARMING UP ON COURSE PRIOR TO ROAD CLOSURE. PRO Village at Easton-Bell Sports reserved for professional competitors that pre-register - go to http://scottsvalleygrandprix.com/pro for more details

title: Back Abbey/Coates Year End Training Ride
description:
this is a non-competitive training ride for USCF licensed racers looping counter-clockwise around and through Carbon Canyon. The event is intended for experienced
riders and the pace will be moderate to fast with several  oderate climbs. The ride will begin and end at the Coffee Bean in the new portion of the downtown Claremont Village.
The course route may be changed at the start by the organizer due to weather or traffic.
course: An approximately 45 mile loop with ~3500 ft of total climbing.  Traffic may be heavy on some sections requiring single file riding.  There will be a re-group point at the park at the top of Carbon Canyon.
registration: In the open public area adjacent to the Coffee Bean on Indian Hill Ave. in downtown Claremont. Registration will be open from 6:30am to 7:00am.
notes: All USCF rules apply. Helmets are mandatory at all times while on your bike. Shirts must cover shoulders. No fixed gears. No tandems. Route is open to traffic and all traffic laws apply. Riders are responsible for their own safety with traffic and other bikes.
directions: From the East or West, exit at Towne Ave. off the 210 Fwy. Go South to Foothill Blvd. and turn left. Continue East until Indian Hill Ave and turn right. The ride will begin at the Coffee Bean on the West side of the road between W. Bonita Ave. and W. 2nd St.
